canonical:
  title: 遊楞伽山
  author: 釋圓鑑
  language: lzh
  text: 舊聞海上有名山幸得遊尋斷宿攀萬壑煙嵐行坐裏千重島嶼顧瞻間義湘庵峻天連棟慈氏堂深石作關避世高栖無此地堪誇倦鳥解知還
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 遊楞伽山
  author: 釋圓鑑
  language: lzh
  text: 舊聞海上有名山。幸得遊尋斷宿攀。萬壑煙嵐行坐裏。千重島嶼顧瞻間。義湘庵峻天連棟。慈氏堂深石作關。避世高栖無此地。堪誇倦鳥解知還。
korean:
  title: 유 능가산
  author: 석원감
  language: kor
  text: |-
    바다 위에 명산이 있단 말 예로 들었더니
    다행히 찾아와 숙원을 풀었구나
    앉거나 거닐거나 만 골짜기의 이내
    앞을 보나 뒤를 보나 겹겹한 섬들
    높디높은 의상암은 지붕이 하늘에 맞닿았고
    자씨당(미륵보살(彌勒菩薩))은 돌로 문을 만들었네
    세상 피해 살려면 이만한 곳 또 있을까
    지친 새 돌아올 줄 안 것 자랑할 만하여라
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_0170_010_0680&viewSync=OT
  footnotes:
  - key: '[주-D001] 지친 새 돌아올 줄 안 것 : '
    value: 도연명(陶淵明)의 귀거래사(歸去來辭)에, “무심한 구름은 메를 나아가고, 새는 날다가 지쳐 돌아올 줄 알았네.”라는 귀절이 있는데, 이것은 자신이 벼슬을 버리고 돌아온 데에 비유하였다.
english:
  title: Journey to Ranggashan
  author: Seok Won-gam
  language: eng
  text: |-
    I had heard the tales of old—
    a famous mountain rising from the sea.
    At last my long desire is fulfilled,
    I have found my way to this sacred place.

    Whether I sit or wander,
    ten thousand gorges wrap me in their mist.
    Each glance reveals more islands,
    layered upon layered beyond count.

    The Uisang Hermitage stands so high
    its roofline touches heaven itself.
    The Hall of Maitreya, deep within,
    has stone as both gate and guardian.

    Where else in this world could one find
    such refuge from its tumult and strife?
    I marvel at the weary bird
    that knows at last the way back home.
  footnotes:
    - Uisang (義湘, 625-702) was a renowned Buddhist monk and founder of the Hwaeom school in Korea. The hermitage bears his name.
    - Maitreya (彌勒菩薩) refers to the Future Buddha, the Hall of Maitreya being a sacred space within the temple complex.
    - The final image of the weary bird knowing its way home alludes to Tao Yuanming's 'Return' (歸去來辭), where the poet compares his retirement from official life to a bird returning when exhausted from flight.
